{
  "texts": [
    "This is significantly worse than the entropy loss when using the same input to an optimal seeded extractor, where m = ⌊-n log 2 (max{p, 1 -p}) -2 log 2 ( 1 ϵ)⌋ i.e.",
    "approximately 0% entropy loss when ϵ is constant.",
    "Other extractors based on this construction, but optimising the output length by recycling unused bits, allow for this entropy loss to be improved, including the Elias and Peres extractor [62] and the generalised Von Neumann extractor [63].",
    "However, they are still unable to achieve the same entropy loss that is possible with seeded extractors, in general.",
    "For completeness, we provide a pseudo-code implementation in Appendix A.7 with computation time O(n)."
  ]
}